subject:

CONTENTMENT (read I Tim 6:6-10)
===================================================================
verse:

If we have food and clothing, we will be content with that.
(I Tim. 6:8)

===================================================================
reflection:

How wonderful it is that the Lord Jesus has met our greatest
needs: our salvation, forgiveness, new life, and peace with
God! We are well supplied with food for our souls conveyed
to us through the means of grace. We have spiritual
clothing: the robe of Christ’s righteousness imparted by
faith. Truly, as Paul said, “Godliness with contentment is
great gain” (I Tim. 6:6) 

===================================================================
prayer:

Lord Jesus, how wonderful it is that You have met our
greatest needs-salvation, forgiveness, new life, and peace
with God. You clothe us with Your robe of righteousness, a
gift of grace that covers our sin and renews our souls. Help
us to live in godliness and contentment, trusting fully in
Your provision and walking faithfully each day as Your
beloved children. May our hearts rejoice in the food of Your
grace and the garments of Your salvation. Amen.  (AI)

===================================================================
